          "data_i18n": null
        },
        {
          "text": "Observed + Predicted",
          "is_correct": false,
          "data_i18n": null
        }
      ],
      "explanation": "A residual = actual value - predicted value. Residuals measure how far data points are from the regression line. The sum of residuals is approximately zero for a least-squares regression. The answer is 'Observed − Predicted'. The other options — 'Predicted − Observed', 'Observed × Predicted', and 'Observed + Predicted' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question."
